	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64393196"><p>I'm reminded of the workers with small rubber hammers doing final alignment of body panels in car factories, these fuselage panels will have a lot more deformation than that. Simply lining up the rivet holes probably takes a fair bit of judiciously applied force and humans are relatively cheap and very flexible robots to solve such problems.</p><p>How much force is too much? How much gap is too much? If he did the simulations to determine how much is too much his opinion are relevant, if he was just on the line and didn't think it was reasonable it doesn't necessarily mean much.</p></div>
	</div>

